WEBVTT

00:02.580 --> 00:04.460
Previously on
"A Million Little Things"...

00:04.460 --> 00:05.580
Yes!

00:05.580 --> 00:07.170
You're not gonna
believe this.

00:07.170 --> 00:09.540
Jon killed himself.

00:09.540 --> 00:11.540
If you hadn't called
to tell me about Jon,

00:11.540 --> 00:13.040
I would be dead
right now.

00:13.040 --> 00:15.580
I had a mouthful of pills
when I answered that phone.

00:15.580 --> 00:16.830
I don't know
anything about you.

00:16.830 --> 00:17.830
I know.
Isn't it great?

00:17.830 --> 00:18.880
Ohh!

00:18.880 --> 00:21.080
Here's the lease. Sign here.

00:21.080 --> 00:22.750
Wait,
why do I have to sign?

00:22.750 --> 00:23.830
Didn't Jon tell you?

00:23.830 --> 00:26.080
He left the restaurant
to both of you.

00:26.080 --> 00:27.000
I'm in love with someone.

00:27.000 --> 00:28.250
What?

00:28.250 --> 00:29.880
She's the mom
of one of my students.

00:29.880 --> 00:32.960
He found your necklace.
It was in his nightstand.

00:32.960 --> 00:35.250
Jon knew about us.
We can't do this.

00:37.920 --> 00:40.460
♪ Think about it ♪

00:40.460 --> 00:44.290
♪ There must be higher love ♪

00:44.290 --> 00:48.670
♪ Down in the heart
or hidden in the stars above ♪

00:48.670 --> 00:51.040
♪ Without it ♪

00:51.040 --> 00:54.290
♪ Life is wasted time ♪

00:54.290 --> 00:56.210
♪ Look inside your heart ♪

00:56.210 --> 01:00.380
♪ I'll look inside mine ♪

01:00.380 --> 01:05.580
♪ Things look so bad
everywhere ♪

01:05.580 --> 01:10.120
♪ In this whole world,
what's fair? ♪

01:10.120 --> 01:10.920
♪ We walk blind ♪

01:10.920 --> 01:12.000
[ Phone vibrates ]

01:12.000 --> 01:15.460
♪ We try to see ♪

01:15.460 --> 01:20.500
♪ Falling behind
in what could be ♪

01:20.500 --> 01:25.000
♪ Bring me a higher love ♪

01:25.000 --> 01:27.540
♪ Where's this higher love ♪

01:27.540 --> 01:30.250
♪ I've been thinking of? ♪

01:30.250 --> 01:31.380
Katherine: The deposition
is Monday at noon.

01:31.380 --> 01:32.460
Tell him I need him
all morning

01:32.460 --> 01:34.420
to prepare him
for cross-examination.

01:34.420 --> 01:35.580
Okay.
[ Phone chimes ]

01:35.580 --> 01:37.790
[ Groans ]
It's not even 7:00.

01:37.790 --> 01:39.790
How long have you been up?

01:39.790 --> 01:42.120
Long enough
to bill two hours.

01:42.120 --> 01:43.080
[ Phone vibrates ]

01:44.540 --> 01:45.210
It's not me.

01:47.170 --> 01:49.000
Ah, believe it or not,
that one's for me.

01:52.250 --> 01:53.710
[ Sighs ]

01:53.710 --> 01:54.880
It's from Jon.

01:57.920 --> 01:59.830
It's an auto-reminder.

01:59.830 --> 02:01.830
Oh, Gary's birthday.

02:01.830 --> 02:03.540
He had us all
save the date.

02:03.540 --> 02:04.960
[ Chuckles ]

02:04.960 --> 02:07.920
God, he thought
of everything.

02:07.920 --> 02:11.210
So, what was he planning
this time?

02:14.170 --> 02:15.380
I'm not sure.

02:15.380 --> 02:17.670
[ Screams, laughs ]

02:17.670 --> 02:19.000
[ Chuckles ]

02:19.000 --> 02:21.000
Uhh, we should probably
get up. [ Chuckles ]

02:21.000 --> 02:23.540
Yes, I agree.
I was being polite.

02:23.540 --> 02:24.920
I thought you were
catching your breath.

02:24.920 --> 02:26.250
Uhh, nope.

02:26.250 --> 02:28.750
My heart rate
is totally normal.

02:28.750 --> 02:30.670
Well, now it is.

02:30.670 --> 02:32.830
Oh, you are
so proud of yourself.

02:32.830 --> 02:34.170
[ Phone vibrates ]
I --

02:34.170 --> 02:36.120
I am just gonna
go out on a limb

02:36.120 --> 02:38.580
and say that I am the best sex
that you've ever --

02:38.580 --> 02:39.790
[ Phone chimes ]

02:39.790 --> 02:44.330
♪♪

02:44.330 --> 02:45.710
Wow.

02:45.710 --> 02:47.670
Something shut you up.

02:47.670 --> 02:49.000
Oh, my gosh.

02:49.000 --> 02:51.250
Can you please send me a link
to whatever that is

02:51.250 --> 02:52.380
so that I can save it
for future use?

02:52.380 --> 02:55.040
I will send you
the link right now.

02:55.040 --> 02:56.000
No! No!
[ Laughing ]

02:56.000 --> 02:57.830
Whoa! Ow! Oh!
[ Thud ]

02:57.830 --> 02:59.380
Sorry.
[ Chuckles ]

02:59.380 --> 03:00.500
Ughh!

03:03.170 --> 03:04.210
[ Door hinges creak ]

03:05.540 --> 03:08.540
Uh...

03:08.540 --> 03:11.330
would you care
to explain...

03:11.330 --> 03:13.080
this?

03:13.080 --> 03:15.540
Uh, p-put him back.

03:15.540 --> 03:17.040
Oh, "him."
He's a boy panda.

03:17.040 --> 03:18.960
What is his name?

03:18.960 --> 03:22.330
His name is
none of your business.

03:22.330 --> 03:25.790
This poor little guy has spent
the last three months

03:25.790 --> 03:29.420
trapped in a box w-with --
what else do we have here?

03:29.420 --> 03:31.580
My goodness, we have a belt.
Okay. Just stop.

03:31.580 --> 03:32.460
Let's just --
I'm serious.

03:32.460 --> 03:33.330
[ Laughs ]

03:36.420 --> 03:38.710
Hey, what -- what happened
to Fun Maggie?

03:38.710 --> 03:41.380
Uhh, she got driven away
by Nosy Gary.

03:41.380 --> 03:43.170
Just stay out of my stuff.

03:44.460 --> 03:47.380
Whoa.
[ Exhales sharply ]

03:47.380 --> 03:48.960
♪♪

03:48.960 --> 03:52.250
What's with her, huh?

03:52.250 --> 03:53.620
I bet you know stuff,
don't you?

03:56.080 --> 03:58.120
You've got
to stop this, Reg.

03:58.120 --> 03:59.960
Regina: I know.
I'm sorry.

03:59.960 --> 04:02.000
I just -- I can't
absorb any more food.

04:02.000 --> 04:03.620
Let's go check out
the restaurant.

04:03.620 --> 04:05.620
I don't know.
Did you read?

04:05.620 --> 04:08.540
They might finally approve the
subway stop two blocks from us.

04:08.540 --> 04:10.210
Do you know what that would do
for business?

04:10.210 --> 04:12.330
No, look, I appreciate
all of this.

04:12.330 --> 04:15.380
Not the cookies,
but your kindness.

04:15.380 --> 04:17.670
It's just, I think right now
I'm better off alone.

04:17.670 --> 04:19.540
No, you're not.

04:19.540 --> 04:21.620
You need to lean on me.

04:21.620 --> 04:24.460
Bother me. Call me.
That is what I am here for.

04:24.460 --> 04:26.500
Otherwise, all I've done
is make you fat.

04:26.500 --> 04:28.380
[ Chuckles ]

04:28.380 --> 04:29.170
Mm.

04:29.170 --> 04:31.500
Did you make Gary cookies?

04:31.500 --> 04:32.420
It's his birthday.

04:32.420 --> 04:35.250
Mm.
[ Chuckles ]

04:35.250 --> 04:37.960
I saw the reminder
on Jon's phone.

04:39.250 --> 04:41.040
Still checking
his phone, huh?

04:42.460 --> 04:44.670
Yeah, I guess I'm just...

04:44.670 --> 04:47.460
hoping someone's gonna call
with an answer.

04:49.080 --> 04:51.330
[ Panting ]

04:51.330 --> 04:59.250
♪♪

04:59.250 --> 05:00.920
-Hey.
-Hey.

05:00.920 --> 05:02.210
What are you doing here?

05:02.210 --> 05:03.290
That's not another smoothie,
is it?

05:03.290 --> 05:04.290
Nah, nah, cookies.

05:04.290 --> 05:05.500
Gina made 'em,
and they're amazing.

05:05.500 --> 05:06.790
Ahh.

05:06.790 --> 05:09.120
You know, this is not
a barter system.

05:09.120 --> 05:11.210
I charge money for therapy,

05:11.210 --> 05:14.750
which I already told you,
I am not offering you.

05:14.750 --> 05:16.170
Did you call Dr. Heller?

05:16.170 --> 05:17.460
I'm more comfortable
with you,

05:17.460 --> 05:19.620
and -- and depression's
your specialty.

05:19.620 --> 05:21.380
I can't be your therapist

05:21.380 --> 05:22.750
and your friend
at the same time.

05:22.750 --> 05:23.750
That's not how it works.

05:23.750 --> 05:25.290
What about friends
with benefits?

05:25.290 --> 05:27.330
Okay, that -- that --
that came out wrong.
[ Scoffs ]

05:27.330 --> 05:28.880
Yeah, everything about this
is wrong.

05:28.880 --> 05:30.120
Okay, wait a minute.
Please.

05:30.120 --> 05:31.460
Do --
Do you have any idea

05:31.460 --> 05:33.170
what it took for me
to come here today?

05:33.170 --> 05:34.620
[ Sighs ]

05:36.330 --> 05:38.170
I mean, I -- I tried
to keep it light,

05:38.170 --> 05:41.080
with the cookies
and everything, but...

05:41.080 --> 05:44.080
I-I don't have the courage to
talk to anyone else about it.

05:45.120 --> 05:46.420
[ Sighs ]

05:47.880 --> 05:50.250
Please.

05:50.250 --> 05:53.710
Whenever you can...

05:53.710 --> 05:55.880
[ Sighs ]
All right. Okay.

05:55.880 --> 05:58.500
The -- Friday at 1:00.
It's my lunch hour.

05:58.500 --> 06:01.210
I will have lunch with you
as a friend,

06:01.210 --> 06:04.830
but you have to promise
to call Dr. Heller.

06:04.830 --> 06:06.210
I promise.
All right.

06:06.210 --> 06:07.290
Thank you.
Yeah.

06:07.290 --> 06:09.380
And -- whoa, whoa.
Leave the cookies.

06:09.380 --> 06:10.920
Oh, right.
Wait a minute.

06:10.920 --> 06:12.380
What, I get one?

06:12.380 --> 06:13.830
No, no, no, no.
Just saving one for Gary.

06:13.830 --> 06:15.040
It's for his birthday.

06:15.040 --> 06:17.250
His birthday. Right.

06:17.250 --> 06:18.420
I'm sure he's told you
how much he hates it.

06:18.420 --> 06:19.620
[ Sighing ] Yeah.

06:20.960 --> 06:22.210
Friday!

06:22.210 --> 06:23.750
[ Door closes ]

06:23.750 --> 06:27.120
[ Noisemaker honks ]

06:27.120 --> 06:29.790
There he is!

06:29.790 --> 06:31.170
Have you been
drinking again?

06:31.170 --> 06:32.920
I just wanted to show you
how much I care, dude.

06:32.920 --> 06:35.290
I know that scares you.

06:35.290 --> 06:37.080
You have any idea
what Jon had in mind?

06:37.080 --> 06:38.880
No.

06:38.880 --> 06:40.710
Pretty sure it didn't involve

06:40.710 --> 06:44.290
recycled decorations from
Theo's fourth birthday party.

06:44.290 --> 06:47.580
Look at you,
doing the walk of shame!

06:47.580 --> 06:48.710
Shame?

06:48.710 --> 06:50.380
No, I just had morning sex.

06:50.380 --> 06:52.040
This is a victory lap.

06:52.040 --> 06:53.790
You are in a broken marriage

06:53.790 --> 06:55.040
having an adulterous affair

06:55.040 --> 06:57.170
with one of your guitar
students' mothers.

06:57.170 --> 07:00.960
Yeah, well, that's done.

07:00.960 --> 07:02.790
"Done"? What are you
talking about, "done"?

07:02.790 --> 07:05.170
I thought you said you were just
pumping the brakes a little.

07:05.170 --> 07:07.790
Man, you were gushing about it
at a hockey game.

07:07.790 --> 07:09.580
It just wasn't meant to be.

07:10.750 --> 07:12.170
I'm sorry, Ed.

07:12.170 --> 07:13.330
But it's tough
to feel bad for you,

07:13.330 --> 07:16.080
because I missed
the whole thing.

07:16.080 --> 07:19.500
♪ Happy birthday ♪

07:19.500 --> 07:20.750
Oh, come on.

07:20.750 --> 07:22.290
Nice!
Eddie: Dude.

07:22.290 --> 07:23.540
[ Both chuckle ]

07:23.540 --> 07:26.380
You too, huh?
Go, Gary. It's your birthday.

07:26.380 --> 07:28.120
You know, the one good thing
about Jon being gone

07:28.120 --> 07:30.460
is that whatever he had planned,
we're not doing.

07:30.460 --> 07:34.170
Which is why I brought love
and a cookie.

07:34.170 --> 07:35.790
Oh, one cookie?
For the three of us?

07:35.790 --> 07:37.250
It's yours, Ed.
The cookie's all yours.

07:37.250 --> 07:40.210
[ Vehicle horn honking ]

07:42.170 --> 07:44.170
Which one of you
is the birthday boy?

07:44.170 --> 07:46.080
Damn it, Jon.

07:54.960 --> 07:56.540
What do you think
Jon planned?

07:56.540 --> 07:57.920
I don't know,
but whatever it is,

07:57.920 --> 07:59.120
we shouldn't be doing it
without him.

07:59.120 --> 08:01.040
Totally.
He should be here.

08:01.040 --> 08:02.210
Just doesn't feel right
without him.

08:02.210 --> 08:03.920
[ Sighs ]
That's because it's wrong.

08:03.920 --> 08:06.460
I knew it.
No, that's -- Rome, don't.

08:06.460 --> 08:08.250
What is he doing?
Don't get inside.

08:08.250 --> 08:10.120
Gentlemen!

08:10.120 --> 08:11.330
Larry -- is it Larry?

08:11.330 --> 08:12.620
Larry: Yes, sir.
Yep.

08:12.620 --> 08:15.790
Larry and his limo
are about to drive us to --

08:15.790 --> 08:16.670
wait for it...

08:18.880 --> 08:20.830
...Bruins Fantasy Camp!

08:21.790 --> 08:24.330
We will be on Bruins ice

08:24.330 --> 08:26.380
playing hockey with some of the
greatest players of all time.

08:26.380 --> 08:28.460
Jon would still want us
to do this, right?

08:28.460 --> 08:29.500
I think he would
come back from the dead

08:29.500 --> 08:30.960
and kill us if we didn't.

08:30.960 --> 08:32.880
We got to do this.
This feels very right.

08:32.880 --> 08:35.250
Yes!

08:35.250 --> 08:39.330
So, they ran out of money
and had to stop construction,

08:39.330 --> 08:42.210
which is fine, because we have
to make it our own anyway.

08:42.210 --> 08:43.580
Mm-hmm.

08:43.580 --> 08:46.670
I don't know, maybe paint
some of the brick white?

08:46.670 --> 08:48.380
Could be nice.

08:48.380 --> 08:50.250
Delilah: Yeah.

08:50.250 --> 08:52.670
Well, I defer to you.
You are the designer.

08:52.670 --> 08:56.000
This is your space.
You could do whatever you want.

08:56.000 --> 08:58.460
So...what do you want?

08:58.460 --> 08:59.580
I don't get it.

08:59.580 --> 09:01.540
He makes sure that you
get the restaurant.

09:01.540 --> 09:04.420
He makes sure
that I'm on the lease.

09:04.420 --> 09:06.670
But he doesn't
leave a note to explain it?

09:08.960 --> 09:11.120
Or tell me why he did it.

09:14.250 --> 09:16.420
Yeah, I don't know, D.
[ Door opens ]

09:17.620 --> 09:19.750
Hello?
Oh, who's that?

09:20.960 --> 09:22.790
[ Gasps ] Maggie! Hi!

09:22.790 --> 09:25.710
I was just
in the neighborhood.
Wow.

09:25.710 --> 09:27.460
Hey. I -- I just --

09:27.460 --> 09:29.420
I don't think
that this is really --

09:29.420 --> 09:31.460
I'm sorry. D, wait.
We're just trying to help.

09:31.460 --> 09:32.830
Delilah: I know.
And keep you company, you know?

09:32.830 --> 09:35.040
And cards on the table,

09:35.040 --> 09:37.120
she may have made
mani/pedi appointments

09:37.120 --> 09:39.290
followed by
deep-cleansing facials

09:39.290 --> 09:41.170
and then lunch reservations

09:41.170 --> 09:43.040
at a place that's
really hard to get into.

09:43.040 --> 09:45.790
♪♪

09:45.790 --> 09:48.380
If you want to help,
I do need to go to Jon's office

09:48.380 --> 09:51.420
and -- and, uh,
go through his stuff.

09:51.420 --> 09:54.420
I just -- I haven't been able
to face it alone.

09:54.420 --> 09:56.460
But, uh...

09:56.460 --> 09:58.790
Then that's
what we'll do instead.

09:58.790 --> 10:00.170
[ Regina and Delilah chuckle ]

10:02.380 --> 10:05.960
Ed, I told you.
The camp supplies all the gear.

10:05.960 --> 10:07.290
But what if Katherine
asks you to do s--

10:07.290 --> 10:09.080
She's gonna want you
to do something.

10:09.080 --> 10:10.210
I have to get
my lucky skates.

10:10.210 --> 10:11.620
How lucky
are they gonna feel

10:11.620 --> 10:13.170
when you get stuck making
chicken tenders for Theo?

10:13.170 --> 10:14.080
Oh.

10:16.170 --> 10:17.620
Wait here.

10:17.620 --> 10:19.670
I'm coming with you 'cause
I don't trust your process.

10:19.670 --> 10:22.880
What part of the chicken
does the tender come from?

10:22.880 --> 10:24.380
Gary:
Here's a radical thought.

10:24.380 --> 10:26.250
When you ask,
why don't you pretend

10:26.250 --> 10:28.330
you have more balls
than a Ken doll?

10:28.330 --> 10:30.460
What are you talking about?
You, your marriage,
the way you walk through it

10:30.460 --> 10:32.500
like you need a permission
slip to do anything.

10:32.500 --> 10:33.670
Hey, guys.

10:33.670 --> 10:35.460
Katherine.

10:35.460 --> 10:37.500
Hello.

10:37.500 --> 10:40.330
Great sweatpants.
They look great. You look great.

10:40.330 --> 10:41.960
Together? Forget about it.

10:41.960 --> 10:42.920
I'll take it from here.

10:42.920 --> 10:43.750
Mm-hmm. [ Clears throat ]

10:43.750 --> 10:45.750
Hey, hon.

10:45.750 --> 10:47.880
Remember how I got that,

10:47.880 --> 10:49.460
um, auto-reminder
from Jon this morning?

10:49.460 --> 10:51.620
Happy birthday.
I know you hate it.

10:51.620 --> 10:53.380
I do!

10:53.380 --> 10:56.080
I normally do.

10:56.080 --> 11:00.880
But then we found out
what he had planned.

11:00.880 --> 11:04.580
It's hockey fantasy camp
with the Bruins at the Garden!

11:04.580 --> 11:07.710
Oh, my God. That is all you guys
ever talk about.

11:07.710 --> 11:10.670
Yeah! So, here's the thing.
I'm supposed to pick up Theo

11:10.670 --> 11:13.170
from his swim lesson
later on today.

11:13.170 --> 11:15.000
But, you know,
since this is obviously

11:15.000 --> 11:16.000
super important to Jon --

11:16.000 --> 11:18.330
I can totally get him.

11:18.330 --> 11:20.750
Jon planned this.
Of course you should go.

11:20.750 --> 11:21.920
Thank you.

11:23.380 --> 11:24.710
I'm gonna get
my lucky skates!

11:24.710 --> 11:26.000
[ Footsteps depart ]

11:27.170 --> 11:29.420
Katherine: So, Gary?

11:29.420 --> 11:30.830
Are we good?

11:33.210 --> 11:35.080
Or do you need me
to sign his permission slip?

11:36.620 --> 11:37.540
[ Taps wall ]

11:41.170 --> 11:43.000
Eddie: [ In distance ]
Thanks, hon! See you later!

11:43.000 --> 11:45.000
[ Door closes ]

11:45.000 --> 11:46.620
[ Pen scratching, hits table ]

11:48.170 --> 11:52.000
[ Phone vibrates ]

11:52.000 --> 11:52.880
Hello?

11:55.710 --> 11:57.170
Oh, I'm sorry,
this is my husband's...

12:00.040 --> 12:01.120
Necklace?

12:02.540 --> 12:03.830
Got my lucky skates.

12:03.830 --> 12:04.960
Got the green light.

12:04.960 --> 12:06.120
Nothing can stop us now.

12:06.120 --> 12:07.500
[ Engine turns over ]

12:07.500 --> 12:09.120
Rome: Guys.

12:09.120 --> 12:10.460
According to this,

12:10.460 --> 12:12.420
chicken tenders
are made from the breast.

12:12.420 --> 12:13.580
It's the nuggets
you got to worry about.

12:13.580 --> 12:16.120
Three words for you --
mechanically separated meat.

12:16.120 --> 12:17.290
You ain't feeding that
to Theo, huh?

12:17.290 --> 12:18.420
Gary: Rome,
put your phone away.

12:18.420 --> 12:19.500
Eddie: Ooh, stop!
I'm sorry.

12:19.500 --> 12:20.670
[ Brakes squeal ]
I forgot my phone.

12:20.670 --> 12:21.960
Eddie...

12:21.960 --> 12:22.920
I'm sorry.
I'll be back in a jiff.

12:22.920 --> 12:24.290
God.

12:24.290 --> 12:26.210
"Jiff." Where's the word
"jiff" come from?

12:26.210 --> 12:28.000
No. I'm not doing
a whole day of this.

12:29.880 --> 12:31.330
[ Door closes ]

12:31.330 --> 12:34.500
Ah! There it is.
Thanks, babe. You're the best.

12:34.500 --> 12:36.290
Hey, what were you doing
at the Hotel Loncar?

12:38.500 --> 12:40.120
[ Chuckles ] What are you
talking about?

12:40.120 --> 12:41.500
Hotel manager just called
to let you know

12:41.500 --> 12:43.290
they couldn't find
your necklace.

12:43.290 --> 12:45.290
What were you doing there?

12:45.290 --> 12:46.920
Oh, the Hotel Loncar?

12:46.920 --> 12:48.460
Yeah, no, I had
lunch there last week

12:48.460 --> 12:50.750
with a friend of mine
from my band days.

12:50.750 --> 12:52.330
He's a drummer.

12:52.330 --> 12:53.420
Never worked with him.
He's too much drama.

12:53.420 --> 12:55.670
His name's Blaze.
Yeah, you get it.

12:55.670 --> 12:57.120
They have a great restaurant.
We ate by the pool.

12:57.120 --> 12:59.710
Really?

12:59.710 --> 13:02.170
Are you...

13:02.170 --> 13:04.750
Are you sure
it wasn't room service?

13:04.750 --> 13:06.830
'Cause the manager
wanted me let you know

13:06.830 --> 13:08.250
that they searched room 312

13:08.250 --> 13:10.170
and your necklace
wasn't there.

13:13.210 --> 13:15.540
So, were you with someone?

13:15.540 --> 13:16.960
No, it wasn't like that.

13:20.460 --> 13:23.620
Are you having an affair?

13:23.620 --> 13:24.580
Katherine, there's so --

13:24.580 --> 13:25.620
Who is it?

13:28.000 --> 13:29.330
It doesn't matter who.

13:29.330 --> 13:30.620
My God.

13:30.620 --> 13:32.620
Is it someone I know?

13:32.620 --> 13:38.830
♪♪

13:38.830 --> 13:40.880
[ Inhales sharply ]

13:42.250 --> 13:43.710
Trust me.
I'm an attorney.

13:43.710 --> 13:45.750
I can find out
who this is by lunch.

13:45.750 --> 13:47.750
Okay.

13:47.750 --> 13:48.920
Listen, just sit down.

13:48.920 --> 13:50.460
I don't want to sit down.

13:50.460 --> 13:53.790
At least give me the respect
of telling me who it is.

13:53.790 --> 13:56.670
[ Breathing heavily ]

13:56.670 --> 13:59.710
"He coined the unit of time
called the 'jiffy'...

13:59.710 --> 14:02.120
What is taking him so long?
He just went in for his phone.

14:02.120 --> 14:04.830
...which was approximately
33.35 picoseconds."

14:04.830 --> 14:08.000
We were inches away from
a clean getaway. [ Sighs ]

14:08.000 --> 14:09.000
"Inches away
from a clean getaway."

14:09.000 --> 14:10.540
What movie is that?
Stop it.

14:10.540 --> 14:15.790
So, every time I was with her,
you were humiliating me.

14:15.790 --> 14:18.540
Acting like
we were all friends

14:18.540 --> 14:21.250
when you and Delilah
were having sex.

14:21.250 --> 14:22.670
Who else knows?

14:22.670 --> 14:23.670
No one knows.

14:23.670 --> 14:25.170
[ Gasps ]

14:25.170 --> 14:29.750
♪♪

14:29.750 --> 14:30.830
Eddie: Katherine.

14:30.830 --> 14:32.080
Katherine.

14:32.080 --> 14:33.460
Get out!
Katherine, please.

14:33.460 --> 14:35.920
Go! Get out!

14:35.920 --> 14:36.920
Hey, Gary!

14:36.920 --> 14:38.670
[ Exhales sharply ]

14:38.670 --> 14:39.920
Gary.

14:39.920 --> 14:40.920
I can't believe you, man.

14:40.920 --> 14:42.920
Gary, please! Wait! Stop.

14:42.920 --> 14:44.080
Just stop!
Get away from that car.

14:44.080 --> 14:45.790
Let me talk, please! Please!
Move, man.

14:45.790 --> 14:47.710
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.
Gentlemen, what's going on?

14:47.710 --> 14:49.120
Easy.

14:49.120 --> 14:50.540
[ Breathing heavily ]
Ask him.

14:50.540 --> 14:51.790
No, Gary.
I just need a second here.

14:51.790 --> 14:53.500
All right, I'll tell you.

14:53.500 --> 14:57.880
The guitar student's mom
that he has been f--

14:57.880 --> 14:59.790
it's Delilah!

14:59.790 --> 15:03.000
Rome. Please.
Give me a second to explain.

15:03.000 --> 15:04.210
You can't explain that.

15:06.620 --> 15:08.920
You can't explain that.

15:08.920 --> 15:10.040
Gary: Let's go, Rome.

15:10.040 --> 15:11.330
Guys.

15:11.330 --> 15:12.620
Please drive.

15:12.620 --> 15:14.540
[ Engine revs ]

15:14.540 --> 15:22.120
♪♪

15:25.880 --> 15:27.120
You just need to calm down.

15:27.120 --> 15:28.500
We both do.
What are you doing?

15:28.500 --> 15:29.290
I am sending an e-mail to Eddie.
He needs to see this.

15:29.290 --> 15:30.460
No, wait, wait, wait.
Don't act out --

15:30.460 --> 15:31.880
Don't touch me.
Don't act out of anger, man.

15:31.880 --> 15:32.960
Oh, that is exactly my plan,

15:32.960 --> 15:34.290
and I encourage you
to get on board.

15:34.290 --> 15:35.040
Why aren't you
mad at Delilah?

15:35.040 --> 15:36.710
Because!

15:36.710 --> 15:37.920
She's not here!

15:37.920 --> 15:40.000
You don't think
I'm pissed? Huh?

15:40.000 --> 15:41.460
You don't think
I'm destroyed by this?

15:41.460 --> 15:43.120
Great. I will sign
the e-mail from both of us.

15:43.120 --> 15:44.670
No, no,
don't send anything,

15:44.670 --> 15:46.330
because you're gonna make
a terrible situation worse,

15:46.330 --> 15:47.620
and I can't afford
to do that anymore.

15:47.620 --> 15:49.580
Hey!

15:49.580 --> 15:52.750
It's too late. Oops.

15:52.750 --> 15:55.920
Eddie slept with one of his
best friends' wives, Rome.

15:55.920 --> 15:56.920
Why don't you call Regina
and see what he did to her?

15:56.920 --> 15:57.920
Dude, there you go!

15:57.920 --> 15:59.290
Oh, oh, I know.
That's good.

15:59.290 --> 16:00.380
Oh, my joke about Eddie
sleeping with your wife --

16:00.380 --> 16:01.210
Oh, you're sharp.
that's inappropriate.

16:01.210 --> 16:03.790
This sucks! I get it.

16:03.790 --> 16:05.000
But we have to push through.

16:05.000 --> 16:07.710
Somehow, you and me
are gonna get in this car,

16:07.710 --> 16:09.250
and we're gonna have
a great day.
How can you say that?

16:09.250 --> 16:10.420
How are we gonna
have a great day?

16:10.420 --> 16:11.460
Are we gonna go to the Garden

16:11.460 --> 16:12.710
and pretend
like nothing happened?

16:12.710 --> 16:15.250
Yeah!

16:15.250 --> 16:17.250
That's what I do, Gary.

16:17.250 --> 16:19.960
That's how I get through
every day.

16:19.960 --> 16:26.960
♪♪

16:26.960 --> 16:29.040
Come on, man.

16:29.040 --> 16:32.500
I can't lose another friend.
Let's go.

16:32.500 --> 16:34.330
[ Vehicle door closes ]

16:34.330 --> 16:39.170
♪♪

16:39.170 --> 16:41.000
Well, you heard him, Larry.

16:41.000 --> 16:42.540
We're going to the Garden.

16:42.540 --> 16:44.960
[ Engine starts ]
Have the best day ever.

16:44.960 --> 16:48.210
Look, I know I have given you
no reason to believe me,

16:48.210 --> 16:49.710
but I am so sorry.

16:49.710 --> 16:51.460
I don't have time for sorry.

16:51.460 --> 16:52.830
I have to finish my brief

16:52.830 --> 16:54.620
because someone
has to pay our mortgage.

16:54.620 --> 16:55.880
I have to pick up Theo.

16:55.880 --> 16:57.880
No, let me get Theo.
I'm gonna pick up Theo.

16:57.880 --> 16:59.710
You're gonna
go somewhere else.

16:59.710 --> 17:00.710
Anywhere else, and figure out

17:00.710 --> 17:02.420
how the hell
you could've done this.

17:03.710 --> 17:05.210
[ Sighs ]

17:05.210 --> 17:07.170
[ Voice breaking ] Forget me.
How could you do this to Theo?

17:10.000 --> 17:12.000
[ Footsteps depart ]

17:12.960 --> 17:13.960
[ Sighs ]

17:13.960 --> 17:16.040
[ Siren wailing in distance ]

17:16.040 --> 17:18.920
Oh, my God.
Are you seeing this?

17:18.920 --> 17:21.120
[ Indistinct conversations ]

17:26.710 --> 17:28.040
Oh, my God.

17:28.040 --> 17:29.880
We are standing right where
Bobby Orr changed

17:29.880 --> 17:33.670
after scoring the winning goal
to win the 1970 Stanley Cup.

17:33.670 --> 17:35.790
Actually, they tore that Garden
down to build this one,

17:35.790 --> 17:37.540
but the point is,

17:37.540 --> 17:39.080
it was probably in a room
just like this.

17:39.080 --> 17:40.420
Dude, look at this!

17:40.420 --> 17:42.170
Personalized jerseys.

17:42.170 --> 17:43.750
[ Chuckling ]
It's like Christmas, man.

17:43.750 --> 17:46.250
Yeah, if just before
you opened your presents,

17:46.250 --> 17:48.380
you found out Santa
had sex with your mother.

17:49.790 --> 17:52.330
No, I understand.
I -- Listen.

17:52.330 --> 17:54.620
Just don't liquidate
anything yet.

17:54.620 --> 17:56.620
Okay, the subway's back on.
[ Elevator bell dings ]

17:56.620 --> 17:59.830
♪♪

17:59.830 --> 18:02.170
[ Quietly ]
I have to call you back.

18:02.170 --> 18:04.170
[ Receiver clicks ]

18:04.170 --> 18:07.830
♪♪

18:07.830 --> 18:09.500
Hey.
Delilah: Hey.

18:09.500 --> 18:12.040
Sorry I-I didn't call.

18:12.040 --> 18:14.170
No, it's okay.

18:14.170 --> 18:15.290
What are you guys doing here?

18:15.290 --> 18:16.790
Just here to help her
pack up Jon's stuff.

18:16.790 --> 18:18.120
Of course.

18:18.120 --> 18:20.170
[ Indistinct conversations,
ringing ]

18:22.540 --> 18:23.830
[ Phone vibrating ]

18:27.750 --> 18:28.960
[ Phone chimes ]

18:28.960 --> 18:31.170
[ Door opens, hinges creak ]

18:31.170 --> 18:37.040
♪♪

18:37.040 --> 18:43.620
♪♪

18:43.620 --> 18:45.500
Why's that still up?

18:45.500 --> 18:48.170
♪♪

18:48.170 --> 18:51.250
The police never came back
to get it.
Ah.

18:51.250 --> 18:52.670
I didn't know what to do.

18:52.670 --> 18:53.710
I'm sorry.
I-I'll take it down.

18:53.710 --> 18:56.790
No, I'll do it.
[ Sighs ]

18:56.790 --> 18:59.080
[ Siren wails in distance ]

18:59.080 --> 19:00.920
Ashley:
I'll go get some boxes.

19:00.920 --> 19:10.170
♪♪

19:10.170 --> 19:19.420
♪♪

19:19.420 --> 19:28.670
♪♪

19:28.670 --> 19:30.620
[ Car alarm blaring ]

19:30.620 --> 19:32.580
[ Sighs ]

19:32.580 --> 19:33.710
♪♪

19:33.710 --> 19:36.920
[ Indistinct conversations ]

19:36.920 --> 19:38.750
[ Tape tearing ]

19:40.420 --> 19:42.000
How great is it
to be wearing a pair of skates

19:42.000 --> 19:44.830
that haven't been worn by a
hundred people before you, huh?

19:44.830 --> 19:47.000
[ Sighs, sniffs ]

19:47.000 --> 19:49.750
We were supposed
to do this the four of us.

19:49.750 --> 19:51.040
[ Exhales sharply ]

19:52.460 --> 19:55.040
Now I got one friend
who can't be here.

19:55.040 --> 19:56.960
Hey, guys.

19:56.960 --> 19:59.920
[ Scoffs ] And another friend
who I don't want here.

19:59.920 --> 20:01.920
How great are birthdays?

20:01.920 --> 20:03.790
Guys, please.
I need to talk to you.

20:03.790 --> 20:05.080
Did you check your e-mail?

20:05.080 --> 20:06.710
What?
I sent you something.

20:06.710 --> 20:08.210
You should watch it.

20:13.120 --> 20:14.380
What -- you already
sent this to us.

20:14.380 --> 20:16.210
Why is he sending this
to me again?

20:16.210 --> 20:17.670
Gary: Oh, what's that?

20:17.670 --> 20:19.250
Is that Katherine calling
to check on your balls?

20:19.250 --> 20:20.380
When does she need
those back?

20:20.380 --> 20:23.330
Jon: Guys,
wives are off-limits.

20:23.330 --> 20:24.330
[ Sighs ]

20:24.330 --> 20:30.000
♪♪

20:30.000 --> 20:31.620
Got to go.

20:31.620 --> 20:37.750
♪♪

20:37.750 --> 20:44.120
♪♪

20:44.120 --> 20:47.040
This is breaking
my heart.

20:47.040 --> 20:49.580
Can't imagine what
it's doing to hers.

20:49.580 --> 20:56.080
♪♪

20:56.080 --> 20:57.920
[ Whistle blows ]

20:57.920 --> 20:58.920
Coach: Bring it in, boys!

21:00.580 --> 21:02.040
All right, well done.

21:02.040 --> 21:03.290
Let's line up here,

21:03.290 --> 21:05.000
and we're gonna
work on the face-off.

21:05.000 --> 21:07.420
Birthday boy,
why don't you go center, huh?

21:07.420 --> 21:10.210
And I'm gonna need
a couple of wingers here.

21:12.830 --> 21:14.790
All right, you ready?

21:14.790 --> 21:16.290
You're seriously
still here?

21:16.290 --> 21:18.880
You've given me
no other choice.

21:18.880 --> 21:23.710
Now, remember, games
are won or lost on the dot.

21:23.710 --> 21:24.920
All right?

21:24.920 --> 21:27.210
Hey, cinch it in.
Smell the puck.

21:28.710 --> 21:29.920
Here we go.

21:29.920 --> 21:32.040
[ Sticks clack ]

21:33.460 --> 21:34.580
Eddie: Gary.

21:34.580 --> 21:36.380
Hey, come on, man.
Don't do this to me.

21:36.380 --> 21:37.500
[ Sticks tapping ]
Don't do this to you?

21:37.500 --> 21:38.830
What about
what you did to Jon?!

21:38.830 --> 21:40.330
[ Grunts ]

21:40.330 --> 21:41.750
Coach: Guys, you're
on the same team, here!

21:41.750 --> 21:43.460
Guys! Seriously.

21:43.460 --> 21:44.710
Get off me!

21:44.710 --> 21:46.000
Don't touch me.

21:46.000 --> 21:48.500
[ Indistinct shouting ]

21:48.500 --> 21:50.830
[ Whistle blowing ]
Coach: Guys. Hey, guys!

21:50.830 --> 21:51.920
[ Both grunting ]

21:51.920 --> 21:53.420
How?!

21:53.420 --> 21:55.290
How could you
sleep with her, Ed?

21:55.290 --> 21:58.120
How could you
sleep with her?

21:58.120 --> 22:00.500
How could you
do this to Jon?

22:04.460 --> 22:07.250
[ Phone ringing, beeps ]
[ Sighs ]

22:07.250 --> 22:09.380
Eddie: Hey, it's me.

22:09.380 --> 22:13.080
I've tried you a couple times,
but you're not picking up.

22:13.080 --> 22:16.290
Look, I didn't want
to do this over voicemail.
[ Sobbing ]

22:16.290 --> 22:19.920
Katherine found out about us.

22:19.920 --> 22:22.670
Gary and Rome know, too.

22:22.670 --> 22:28.460
♪♪

22:28.460 --> 22:34.250
♪♪

22:34.250 --> 22:37.040
Yeah, I just called Rome
to see how the day's going.

22:37.040 --> 22:40.000
♪♪

22:40.000 --> 22:42.460
How could you?

22:42.460 --> 22:48.040
♪♪

22:48.040 --> 22:49.000
Maybe I should leave you guys...

22:49.000 --> 22:51.040
No. Don't.

22:52.380 --> 22:54.000
Let's just do this.

22:54.000 --> 22:55.750
[ Night Flight's "Storm" plays ]

22:55.750 --> 22:59.540
♪♪

22:59.540 --> 23:00.920
[ Sighs ]

23:00.920 --> 23:08.170
♪♪

23:08.170 --> 23:11.750
♪ Order, order, nobody can see ♪

23:11.750 --> 23:15.330
♪ All the leaves are falling
from her authenticity ♪

23:15.330 --> 23:18.830
[ Doorbell rings ]
♪ Corner, corner,
everything you know ♪

23:18.830 --> 23:25.080
♪ Stick it in a pile where
the innocence of love can grow ♪

23:25.080 --> 23:26.290
[ Door opens ]

23:26.290 --> 23:28.040
Katherine!

23:28.040 --> 23:29.880
Oh, you're home.

23:29.880 --> 23:31.210
I was running errands
on my lunch break,

23:31.210 --> 23:32.250
and I wanted
to return this.

23:32.250 --> 23:33.500
Thank you
for lending it to me.

23:33.500 --> 23:35.170
Oh, no, it's fine.
I told you to keep it.

23:35.170 --> 23:37.040
It looks beautiful on you.

23:37.040 --> 23:40.670
♪ Saw her, saw her,
pickled in the light ♪
That is so sweet.

23:40.670 --> 23:43.330
♪ Fickle as her ghosts
as she wriggles in the night ♪
Is Eddie here?

23:43.330 --> 23:46.080
Yes! He's, uh --
Eddie!

23:46.080 --> 23:48.620
He's here for, um,
Sophie's guitar lesson.

23:48.620 --> 23:51.620
♪ Standing by the pillars
of dishonesty and greed ♪

23:51.620 --> 23:53.290
Hey, hon.

23:53.290 --> 23:57.420
♪♪

23:57.420 --> 24:01.580
♪ And greed ♪

24:01.580 --> 24:08.620
♪♪

24:10.670 --> 24:13.920
[ Tape creaking ]

24:17.750 --> 24:19.420
[ Creaking continues ]

24:20.670 --> 24:22.080
Say it.

24:24.170 --> 24:26.460
Why won't somebody
just say it?

24:26.460 --> 24:29.120
♪♪

24:29.120 --> 24:30.670
Just say it!

24:30.670 --> 24:32.620
Say what?

24:32.620 --> 24:35.290
I need to know where it is.

24:35.290 --> 24:38.120
Delilah. Delilah.
What are you looking for?

24:38.120 --> 24:39.210
Maybe I can help you find it.

24:39.210 --> 24:41.750
He must've left
something, right?

24:41.750 --> 24:43.120
Where is it?
Delilah, where's what?

24:43.120 --> 24:44.460
The note. The note.

24:44.460 --> 24:47.000
The note that tells me
to go to hell!

24:47.000 --> 24:49.790
So I know that's why he did it.
[ Breathing heavily ]

24:49.790 --> 24:51.040
That's what you're
all thinking, isn't it?

24:53.290 --> 24:55.080
Right? Isn't it?
That I killed him?

24:57.000 --> 24:59.210
Say it.

24:59.210 --> 25:00.710
Just say it.

25:01.880 --> 25:03.170
Say it!

25:03.170 --> 25:05.920
[ Boxes clatter ]

25:05.920 --> 25:08.290
[ Footsteps depart ]

25:08.290 --> 25:09.080
[ Sighs ]

25:13.040 --> 25:15.380
Look, I screwed up.
I know.

25:15.380 --> 25:17.210
Yeah, royally.

25:17.210 --> 25:18.830
Even for you, Ed,
this is a -- it's a big one.

25:18.830 --> 25:22.330
I know what I did was wrong.

25:22.330 --> 25:25.040
I-I broke the biggest
guy code there is.

25:25.040 --> 25:27.830
And I am so sorry.

25:27.830 --> 25:29.080
And there's nothing
I can say,

25:29.080 --> 25:31.290
except I wish it didn't happen,
but it did.

25:31.290 --> 25:33.460
[ Stick thuds ]
And...

25:33.460 --> 25:36.380
believe me.
We fought it every single day.

25:36.380 --> 25:38.000
[ Indistinct shouting
in distance ]

25:38.000 --> 25:40.290
Until...

25:40.290 --> 25:42.580
Until what?

25:42.580 --> 25:44.250
Until we fell in love.

25:48.380 --> 25:50.250
And we were gonna
tell everybody.

25:50.250 --> 25:52.540
I swear to you.

25:55.710 --> 25:57.290
And then...

25:57.290 --> 26:02.250
♪♪

26:02.250 --> 26:07.250
And I can't help but think
that maybe he already knew.

26:07.250 --> 26:11.290
That maybe that's why.

26:11.290 --> 26:13.080
I hope that's why
he killed himself.

26:13.080 --> 26:14.710
Oh, damn, Gary.

26:17.080 --> 26:19.460
At least then I'd know why.

26:19.460 --> 26:22.920
♪♪

26:26.250 --> 26:28.380
Ashley,
did Jon know about this?

26:28.380 --> 26:30.750
I mean, did he ever
say anything to you?

26:30.750 --> 26:32.540
No.

26:32.540 --> 26:34.330
He didn't know.

26:37.290 --> 26:38.500
At least,
I don't think he did.

26:43.380 --> 26:45.290
[ Sighs ] I don't know.
People make mistakes.

26:45.290 --> 26:48.330
This is not a mistake.

26:48.330 --> 26:51.750
Mistakes are things
that happen by accident.

26:51.750 --> 26:53.040
Gina.

26:53.040 --> 26:54.080
I mean, it makes
a big difference, though,

26:54.080 --> 26:55.960
doesn't it?

26:55.960 --> 26:57.790
I mean, he killed himself.

26:59.880 --> 27:03.540
All right, fellas, we're gonna
play a little four-on-four.

27:03.540 --> 27:05.500
Where's your fourth?

27:05.500 --> 27:07.540
We're down a man.
Do you want a sub?

27:07.540 --> 27:09.540
No, we'll be fine.

27:09.540 --> 27:11.790
This one brought
his lucky skates.

27:11.790 --> 27:16.460
[ Indistinct chatter ]

27:16.460 --> 27:18.210
Man: Let's go.

27:18.210 --> 27:21.250
[ Sticks clacking ]

27:21.250 --> 27:22.670
Come on. Get your butts in gear.
Let's go!

27:22.670 --> 27:24.040
Rome: Eddie, stay with him.
Stay with him!

27:24.040 --> 27:27.000
Man: Hey, play a little defense,
why don't you?

27:27.000 --> 27:29.620
[ Buzzer ]
Man: Well done, boys.
Well done!

27:29.620 --> 27:31.380
[ Cheering ]

27:31.380 --> 27:32.920
So glad we stopped by
to get those.

27:35.790 --> 27:38.210
[ Vehicle approaches ]

27:38.210 --> 27:47.000
♪♪

27:47.000 --> 27:55.790
♪♪

27:55.790 --> 28:04.620
♪♪

28:04.620 --> 28:06.620
[ Sighs ]

28:06.620 --> 28:15.000
♪♪

28:15.000 --> 28:17.330
I'm so sorry, Katherine.

28:17.330 --> 28:23.580
♪♪

28:23.580 --> 28:28.170
I was in a bad place in --
in my marriage, in my life,

28:28.170 --> 28:32.330
but I shouldn't have
complicated yours.

28:32.330 --> 28:35.000
I didn't mean
to hurt anybody, but...

28:36.000 --> 28:37.210
[ Sniffles ]

28:37.210 --> 28:40.290
All I've done is...

28:40.290 --> 28:42.290
is hurt everybody.

28:42.290 --> 28:47.540
♪♪

28:47.540 --> 28:52.670
♪♪

28:52.670 --> 28:55.920
You know,
when I found out today,

28:55.920 --> 28:58.080
I just felt so alone.

29:00.960 --> 29:06.620
And I wanted to call the one
person who understood me,

29:06.620 --> 29:09.880
who understood
why I worked so hard,

29:09.880 --> 29:13.120
why I'm not always home.

29:16.040 --> 29:17.710
I wanted to call Jon.

29:21.750 --> 29:24.960
I don't work hard
because I want to.

29:24.960 --> 29:29.210
I work hard because I'm making
a sacrifice for my family.

29:33.880 --> 29:36.210
And Jon understood that.

29:40.290 --> 29:42.790
I came here today
to yell at you.

29:45.790 --> 29:49.210
But I can't...

29:49.210 --> 29:51.750
because I think you've already
paid the ultimate price.

29:51.750 --> 29:58.040
♪♪

29:58.040 --> 29:59.920
Man: Good, good.
Man #2: Come on. Come on.

29:59.920 --> 30:02.120
[ Indistinct chatter ]

30:04.460 --> 30:05.540
Ohh!

30:05.540 --> 30:06.790
Yeah, Gary!

30:08.580 --> 30:12.420
[ Indistinct shouting ]

30:12.420 --> 30:13.620
[ Buzzer ]

30:13.620 --> 30:15.620
Whoo!

30:15.620 --> 30:17.540
[ Cheering ]

30:17.540 --> 30:20.250
All right, fellas.
We're tied at two up.

30:20.250 --> 30:22.040
Next goal wins.

30:22.040 --> 30:25.460
[ Indistinct chatter ]

30:25.460 --> 30:34.710
♪♪

30:34.710 --> 30:44.420
♪♪

30:44.420 --> 30:45.920
Let's thank him
for your birthday present.

30:45.920 --> 30:49.460
♪♪

30:49.460 --> 30:59.540
♪♪

30:59.540 --> 31:09.460
♪♪

31:09.460 --> 31:19.250
♪♪

31:19.250 --> 31:20.040
Now!

31:20.040 --> 31:21.290
Ed, put it in!

31:21.290 --> 31:25.580
♪♪

31:25.580 --> 31:26.620
Yeah!

31:26.620 --> 31:29.500
[ Buzzer ]
[ Cheering ]

31:29.500 --> 31:30.790
Aah!

31:30.790 --> 31:32.420
Whoo!

31:32.420 --> 31:35.710
[ Laughs ]

31:35.710 --> 31:37.790
Fellas!

31:39.580 --> 31:42.460
Sauce and all!
Good pass.

31:42.460 --> 31:44.000
♪♪

31:44.000 --> 31:45.580
[ Laughs ]

31:45.580 --> 31:49.330
♪♪

31:49.330 --> 31:50.580
[ Sighs ]

31:50.580 --> 31:51.880
[ Sniffs ]

31:54.330 --> 31:55.960
Hey, Gare,
where you going?

32:00.210 --> 32:03.120
What do you think this is, Ed?

32:03.120 --> 32:05.750
The end of some sports movie
where we all come together,

32:05.750 --> 32:08.290
beat the other guys, and...

32:08.290 --> 32:10.540
everything's
healed between us?

32:10.540 --> 32:13.250
♪♪

32:13.250 --> 32:15.040
I don't think so.

32:15.040 --> 32:17.830
This is real life.

32:17.830 --> 32:20.750
What you did
is unforgivable.

32:20.750 --> 32:24.040
♪♪

32:27.420 --> 32:29.620
[ Sighs ]

32:29.620 --> 32:31.620
Good game, gentlemen.

32:31.620 --> 32:33.500
I'll find my own way home.

32:38.000 --> 32:42.670
♪♪

32:42.670 --> 32:46.210
Listen, Eddie.

32:46.210 --> 32:48.790
People have affairs
all the time.

32:48.790 --> 32:50.500
And people
find out about 'em.

32:52.750 --> 32:54.460
They don't usually
kill themselves.

32:54.460 --> 32:59.290
♪♪

32:59.290 --> 33:01.880
And...

33:01.880 --> 33:04.880
And even -- even if
it was a part of it,

33:04.880 --> 33:08.620
it wasn't the whole thing.

33:08.620 --> 33:10.210
You can --
You can take that from me.

33:12.790 --> 33:14.250
It wasn't one thing.

33:16.380 --> 33:18.080
It was probably
a million things.

33:20.080 --> 33:21.500
[ Sighs ]

33:23.080 --> 33:25.420
[ Buzzer ]

33:25.420 --> 33:28.080
[ Indistinct conversations
in distance ]

33:28.080 --> 33:29.670
[ Sighs ]

33:29.670 --> 33:37.620
♪♪

33:37.620 --> 33:39.290
Hey.

33:39.290 --> 33:41.210
Thought you could use
a little cheering up.

33:42.420 --> 33:45.580
That's very sweet.

33:45.580 --> 33:47.790
Although, people have got
to stop coming by my place

33:47.790 --> 33:50.040
just because
it's my birthday.

33:50.040 --> 33:52.380
Well, maybe next time
you should let people
know it's your birthday

33:52.380 --> 33:54.540
so they don't have
to make a separate trip.

33:54.540 --> 33:56.960
Really?

33:56.960 --> 33:58.500
I didn't tell you
about my birthday?

33:58.500 --> 34:00.540
Yeah. [ Chuckles ]
That's funny.

34:00.540 --> 34:02.210
You haven't
told me anything.

34:02.210 --> 34:04.040
Except to keep my hands
off your panda.

34:04.040 --> 34:06.000
What are you so scared of?

34:06.000 --> 34:07.880
Okay, this is not
about me.

34:07.880 --> 34:09.500
This is about you.

34:09.500 --> 34:11.420
This is just
supposed to be fun.

34:11.420 --> 34:13.620
Yeah.

34:13.620 --> 34:16.250
Well, right now,
this is not fun,

34:16.250 --> 34:18.420
so maybe come back
when it is.

34:18.420 --> 34:20.210
[ Man speaking
indistinctly in distance ]

34:22.710 --> 34:23.460
All right.

34:23.460 --> 34:31.540
♪♪

34:31.540 --> 34:35.170
[ Phone vibrating ]

34:35.170 --> 34:38.290
♪♪

34:38.290 --> 34:39.710
[ Phone chimes ]

34:39.710 --> 34:41.500
Hello? [ Sighs ]

34:43.330 --> 34:44.880
[ Whispering ]
Why are you calling this number?

34:44.880 --> 34:47.790
[ Sighs ]

34:47.790 --> 34:51.000
Uh, I...

34:51.000 --> 34:52.960
needed to hear his voice.

34:53.920 --> 34:54.960
[ Sniffles ]

34:57.790 --> 34:59.380
How you doing?

34:59.380 --> 35:01.830
Not great.

35:01.830 --> 35:03.670
Yeah, me neither.

35:06.750 --> 35:09.000
He left me a voicemail.

35:09.000 --> 35:10.420
What?

35:10.420 --> 35:12.710
At the hotel --
when we didn't pick up.

35:12.710 --> 35:14.790
[ Inhales sharply ] Wait,
you're just telling me this --

35:14.790 --> 35:17.040
Wh-- [ Sniffles ]
What did he say?

35:18.000 --> 35:20.830
He said...

35:20.830 --> 35:23.540
"Do me a favor.

35:23.540 --> 35:25.500
Love each other."

35:25.500 --> 35:27.420
"Love each other"?
That's it?

35:29.960 --> 35:31.420
Did he mean...

35:31.420 --> 35:33.670
Did he mean you and me?

35:33.670 --> 35:34.670
Maybe.

35:34.670 --> 35:36.670
Maybe he meant all of us.

35:38.670 --> 35:42.170
[ Sniffles ]
Regina won't even talk to me.

35:45.330 --> 35:46.710
[ Sighs ]

35:46.710 --> 35:49.170
I'm so sorry.

35:51.580 --> 35:54.040
I have to go.

35:54.040 --> 35:55.830
Okay.

35:55.830 --> 35:59.460
[ Elbow's "Jesus is
a Rochdale Girl" plays ]

35:59.460 --> 36:02.170
♪ I have a single heartbreak ♪

36:03.830 --> 36:05.080
[ Phone beeps ]

36:05.080 --> 36:07.290
♪ I celebrate and mourn ♪

36:09.620 --> 36:12.080
[ Phone chimes ]
♪ A single shining sister ♪

36:14.580 --> 36:15.920
♪ And all the tricks of dawn ♪

36:15.920 --> 36:17.210
[ Sighs ]

36:18.920 --> 36:21.670
♪ A single yellow duvet ♪

36:24.040 --> 36:26.460
♪ A single switch to flick ♪

36:26.460 --> 36:28.620
[ Sighs ]

36:28.620 --> 36:32.330
♪ But a thousand boxes
yet to take ♪

36:32.330 --> 36:33.880
[ Sniffles ]

36:33.880 --> 36:38.920
♪♪

36:41.040 --> 36:43.620
[ Water running, dishes clink ]

36:43.620 --> 36:53.120
♪♪

36:53.120 --> 36:56.710
I know it doesn't help,

36:56.710 --> 36:59.670
but just so you do know,
it's over.

36:59.670 --> 37:05.500
♪♪

37:05.500 --> 37:11.580
♪♪

37:11.580 --> 37:13.580
I'll do whatever you want.

37:13.580 --> 37:21.960
♪♪

37:21.960 --> 37:24.250
Do you love her?

37:24.250 --> 37:31.540
♪♪

37:31.540 --> 37:38.620
♪♪

37:38.620 --> 37:40.330
[ Sighs ]

37:40.330 --> 37:45.830
♪♪

37:45.830 --> 37:51.250
♪♪

37:51.250 --> 37:53.120
[ Doorbell rings ]

37:53.120 --> 37:55.540
Delilah: Hey.

37:55.540 --> 37:57.670
[ Insects chirping ]

37:57.670 --> 38:04.920
♪♪

38:04.920 --> 38:06.960
Why wasn't he enough?

38:10.500 --> 38:12.710
He was enough for me.

38:12.710 --> 38:14.250
Yeah.

38:16.830 --> 38:20.000
That's just it, Gary.

38:20.000 --> 38:22.460
He was there for everybody.

38:22.460 --> 38:26.000
He was everything
to everyone.

38:26.000 --> 38:29.750
Which was great,
except that I...

38:29.750 --> 38:31.960
I just got forgotten.

38:36.830 --> 38:39.330
I really hate my birthday.

38:39.330 --> 38:40.830
I know.

38:40.830 --> 38:43.040
I didn't used to.

38:43.040 --> 38:45.420
I remember that feeling,
waking up and realizing,

38:45.420 --> 38:47.290
"Today's the day.
Today is my birthday,"

38:47.290 --> 38:50.290
especially as a kid.
[ Exhales sharply ]

38:50.290 --> 38:54.250
When I was 7, my parents
threw this huge party.

38:54.250 --> 38:55.920
Whole grade came over.

38:55.920 --> 38:59.710
Not just my class --
the whole grade.

38:59.710 --> 39:01.500
And they hired a magician.

39:01.500 --> 39:02.670
You hate magicians.

39:02.670 --> 39:04.080
Now I hate magicians.

39:04.080 --> 39:06.790
[ Chuckles ]
But back then, maa-aan.

39:08.170 --> 39:09.670
That morning, my parents
got into a huge fight.

39:09.670 --> 39:11.210
It was a real blowout.

39:11.210 --> 39:15.000
In their bedroom, and all
those kids could hear them.

39:17.210 --> 39:19.710
And I guess they stayed together
for a couple months after that,

39:19.710 --> 39:21.460
but that was the day
that I knew

39:21.460 --> 39:23.830
that my parents' marriage
was over.

39:23.830 --> 39:29.170
♪♪

39:29.170 --> 39:30.960
And when I blew out
my candles,

39:30.960 --> 39:33.210
I didn't wish
for them to stay together.

39:33.210 --> 39:37.080
♪♪

39:37.080 --> 39:39.120
I just wished
for us to be happy.

39:41.210 --> 39:43.330
And then I promised myself

39:43.330 --> 39:45.250
that I would
never get married,

39:45.250 --> 39:48.830
because that is not
what I wanted.

39:48.830 --> 39:50.960
♪♪

39:50.960 --> 39:55.420
But then I saw you and Jon,

39:55.420 --> 39:57.000
and damn it, D,

39:57.000 --> 40:00.330
you made me believe in it
all over again.

40:00.330 --> 40:02.960
♪♪

40:02.960 --> 40:08.040
Jon and I, we were --
we were that amazing couple.

40:08.040 --> 40:10.880
Until we just -- we weren't.

40:10.880 --> 40:12.250
And that --
that doesn't mean

40:12.250 --> 40:14.250
that you shouldn't
try to get that.

40:14.250 --> 40:17.790
♪♪

40:17.790 --> 40:21.880
If I -- If I could fall in love
with him all over again...

40:24.580 --> 40:26.500
...I would.

40:26.500 --> 40:31.000
[ Ryan Adams' "Lucky Now"
plays ]

40:31.000 --> 40:34.210
Can I show you something?

40:34.210 --> 40:37.290
♪ I don't remember,
were we wild and young? ♪

40:37.290 --> 40:38.540
[ Door closes ]

40:38.540 --> 40:42.580
[ Sighs ]
♪ All that's faded into memory ♪

40:42.580 --> 40:46.460
♪ I feel like somebody
I don't know ♪

40:46.460 --> 40:49.670
Come on, D. What is this?
♪ Are we really
who we used to be? ♪

40:49.670 --> 40:53.500
Just -- it got here
a couple of hours ago.

40:53.500 --> 40:54.880
Apparently,
the limo driver

40:54.880 --> 40:58.250
was gonna drop you guys
off here and...

40:58.250 --> 41:02.120
♪ And the dark
will bring you down ♪

41:02.120 --> 41:05.540
♪ And the night
will break your heart ♪

41:05.540 --> 41:08.380
♪ But only if you're lucky now ♪

41:08.380 --> 41:11.290
What are you doing?

41:11.290 --> 41:14.540
Just got to
light the candles.

41:14.540 --> 41:15.620
[ Chuckles ]

41:15.620 --> 41:18.500
♪♪

41:18.500 --> 41:20.330
♪ Waiting outside
while you find your keys ♪

41:20.330 --> 41:22.210
Five.

41:22.210 --> 41:23.540
It's all I got.

41:23.540 --> 41:26.500
♪ Like bags of trash
in the blackening snow ♪

41:26.500 --> 41:30.170
♪ City of neon
and toes that freeze ♪

41:30.170 --> 41:33.540
You know,
not for nothing --

41:33.540 --> 41:35.830
how upset should I be that
you picked Eddie and not me?

41:35.830 --> 41:38.120
[ Chuckles ]
♪ We've got nothing
and nowhere ♪

41:38.120 --> 41:42.170
♪ And the lights
will draw you in ♪

41:42.170 --> 41:43.960
♪ And the dark
will take you down ♪

41:43.960 --> 41:46.040
Make a wish.

41:46.040 --> 41:48.290
[ Sighs ]
I don't wanna.
♪ The night will
break your heart ♪

41:48.290 --> 41:49.330
Come on.

41:49.330 --> 41:51.920
♪ Only if you're lucky now ♪

41:51.920 --> 41:53.830
What are you
gonna wish for?

41:53.830 --> 41:57.670
♪ If the lights
will draw you in ♪

41:57.670 --> 42:01.620
♪ And the dark
will take you down ♪

42:01.620 --> 42:05.040
The same thing I've been wishing
for since I was 7.
♪ But love will
mend your heart ♪

42:05.040 --> 42:08.080
♪ But only if
you're lucky now ♪

42:13.250 --> 42:17.710
♪♪

42:17.710 --> 42:19.460
Damn it, Jon.

42:24.000 --> 42:33.040
♪♪

42:33.040 --> 42:42.040
♪♪

42:42.040 --> 42:51.080
♪♪

42:52.540 --> 42:54.540
That's my boy!

42:54.540 --> 42:59.120
♪♪
